59/* X509 v3 extension utilities */
60
61#include <stdio.h>
62
63#include <openssl/conf.h>
64#include <openssl/err.h>
65#include <openssl/mem.h>
66#include <openssl/obj.h>
67#include <openssl/x509v3.h>
68
69#include "ext_dat.h"
70static STACK_OF(X509V3_EXT_METHOD) *ext_list = NULL;
71
72static void ext_list_free(X509V3_EXT_METHOD *ext);
73
74static int ext_stack_cmp(const X509V3_EXT_METHOD **a,
75 const X509V3_EXT_METHOD **b)
76{
77 return ((*a)->ext_nid - (*b)->ext_nid);
78}
79
80int X509V3_EXT_add(X509V3_EXT_METHOD *ext)
81{
82 if (!ext_list && !(ext_list = sk_X509V3_EXT_METHOD_new(ext_stack_cmp))) {
83 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
84 ext_list_free(ext);
85 return 0;
86 }
87 if (!sk_X509V3_EXT_METHOD_push(ext_list, ext)) {
88 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
89 ext_list_free(ext);
90 return 0;
91 }
92 return 1;
93}
94
95static int ext_cmp(const void *void_a, const void *void_b)
96{
97 const X509V3_EXT_METHOD **a = (const X509V3_EXT_METHOD **)void_a;
98 const X509V3_EXT_METHOD **b = (const X509V3_EXT_METHOD **)void_b;
99 return ext_stack_cmp(a, b);
100}
101
102const X509V3_EXT_METHOD *X509V3_EXT_get_nid(int nid)
103{
104 X509V3_EXT_METHOD tmp;
105 const X509V3_EXT_METHOD *t = &tmp, *const *ret;
106 size_t idx;
107
108 if (nid < 0)
109 return NULL;
110 tmp.ext_nid = nid;
111 ret =
112 bsearch(&t, standard_exts, STANDARD_EXTENSION_COUNT,
113 sizeof(X509V3_EXT_METHOD *), ext_cmp);
114 if (ret)
115 return *ret;
116 if (!ext_list)
117 return NULL;
118
119 sk_X509V3_EXT_METHOD_sort(ext_list);
120 if (!sk_X509V3_EXT_METHOD_find(ext_list, &idx, &tmp))
121 return NULL;
122 return sk_X509V3_EXT_METHOD_value(ext_list, idx);
123}
124
125const X509V3_EXT_METHOD *X509V3_EXT_get(const X509_EXTENSION *ext)
126{
127 int nid;
128 if ((nid = OBJ_obj2nid(ext->object)) == NID_undef)
129 return NULL;
130 return X509V3_EXT_get_nid(nid);
131}
132
133int X509V3_EXT_free(int nid, void *ext_data)
134{
135 const X509V3_EXT_METHOD *ext_method = X509V3_EXT_get_nid(nid);
136 if (ext_method == NULL) {
137 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, X509V3_R_CANNOT_FIND_FREE_FUNCTION);
138 return 0;
139 }
140
141 if (ext_method->it != NULL)
142 ASN1_item_free(ext_data, ASN1_ITEM_ptr(ext_method->it));
143 else if (ext_method->ext_free != NULL)
144 ext_method->ext_free(ext_data);
145 else {
146 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, X509V3_R_CANNOT_FIND_FREE_FUNCTION);
147 return 0;
148 }
149
150 return 1;
151}
152
153int X509V3_EXT_add_list(X509V3_EXT_METHOD *extlist)
154{
155 for (; extlist->ext_nid != -1; extlist++)
156 if (!X509V3_EXT_add(extlist))
157 return 0;
158 return 1;
159}
160
161int X509V3_EXT_add_alias(int nid_to, int nid_from)
162{
163 const X509V3_EXT_METHOD *ext;
164 X509V3_EXT_METHOD *tmpext;
165
166 if (!(ext = X509V3_EXT_get_nid(nid_from))) {
167 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, X509V3_R_EXTENSION_NOT_FOUND);
168 return 0;
169 }
170 if (!
171 (tmpext =
172 (X509V3_EXT_METHOD *)OPENSSL_malloc(sizeof(X509V3_EXT_METHOD)))) {
173 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
174 return 0;
175 }
176 *tmpext = *ext;
177 tmpext->ext_nid = nid_to;
178 tmpext->ext_flags |= X509V3_EXT_DYNAMIC;
179 return X509V3_EXT_add(tmpext);
180}
181
182void X509V3_EXT_cleanup(void)
183{
184 sk_X509V3_EXT_METHOD_pop_free(ext_list, ext_list_free);
185 ext_list = NULL;
186}
187
188static void ext_list_free(X509V3_EXT_METHOD *ext)
189{
190 if (ext->ext_flags & X509V3_EXT_DYNAMIC)
191 OPENSSL_free(ext);
192}

194/*
195 * Legacy function: we don't need to add standard extensions any more because
196 * they are now kept in ext_dat.h.
197 */
198
199int X509V3_add_standard_extensions(void)
200{
201 return 1;
202}
203
204/* Return an extension internal structure */
205
206void *X509V3_EXT_d2i(const X509_EXTENSION *ext)
207{
208 const X509V3_EXT_METHOD *method;
209 const unsigned char *p;
210
211 if (!(method = X509V3_EXT_get(ext)))
212 return NULL;
213 p = ext->value->data;
214 if (method->it)
215 return ASN1_item_d2i(NULL, &p, ext->value->length,
216 ASN1_ITEM_ptr(method->it));
217 return method->d2i(NULL, &p, ext->value->length);
218}
219
220void *X509V3_get_d2i(const STACK_OF(X509_EXTENSION) *extensions, int nid,
221 int *out_critical, int *out_idx)
222{
223 int lastpos;
224 size_t i;
225 X509_EXTENSION *ex, *found_ex = NULL;
226 if (!extensions) {
227 if (out_idx)
228 *out_idx = -1;
229 if (out_critical)
230 *out_critical = -1;
231 return NULL;
232 }
233 if (out_idx)
234 lastpos = *out_idx + 1;
235 else
236 lastpos = 0;
237 if (lastpos < 0)
238 lastpos = 0;
239 for (i = lastpos; i < sk_X509_EXTENSION_num(extensions); i++) {
240 ex = sk_X509_EXTENSION_value(extensions, i);
241 if (OBJ_obj2nid(ex->object) == nid) {
242 if (out_idx) {
243 /* TODO(https://crbug.com/boringssl/379): Consistently reject
244 * duplicate extensions. */
245 *out_idx = i;
246 found_ex = ex;
247 break;
248 } else if (found_ex) {
249 /* Found more than one */
250 if (out_critical)
251 *out_critical = -2;
252 return NULL;
253 }
254 found_ex = ex;
255 }
256 }
257 if (found_ex) {
258 /* Found it */
259 if (out_critical)
260 *out_critical = X509_EXTENSION_get_critical(found_ex);
261 return X509V3_EXT_d2i(found_ex);
262 }
263
264 /* Extension not found */
265 if (out_idx)
266 *out_idx = -1;
267 if (out_critical)
268 *out_critical = -1;
269 return NULL;
270}
271
272/*
273 * This function is a general extension append, replace and delete utility.
274 * The precise operation is governed by the 'flags' value. The 'crit' and
275 * 'value' arguments (if relevant) are the extensions internal structure.
276 */
277
278int X509V3_add1_i2d(STACK_OF(X509_EXTENSION) **x, int nid, void *value,
279 int crit, unsigned long flags)
280{
281 int errcode, extidx = -1;
282 X509_EXTENSION *ext = NULL, *extmp;
283 STACK_OF(X509_EXTENSION) *ret = NULL;
284 unsigned long ext_op = flags & X509V3_ADD_OP_MASK;
285
286 /*
287 * If appending we don't care if it exists, otherwise look for existing
288 * extension.
289 */
290 if (ext_op != X509V3_ADD_APPEND)
291 extidx = X509v3_get_ext_by_NID(*x, nid, -1);
292
293 /* See if extension exists */
294 if (extidx >= 0) {
295 /* If keep existing, nothing to do */
296 if (ext_op == X509V3_ADD_KEEP_EXISTING)
297 return 1;
298 /* If default then its an error */
299 if (ext_op == X509V3_ADD_DEFAULT) {
300 errcode = X509V3_R_EXTENSION_EXISTS;
301 goto err;
302 }
303 /* If delete, just delete it */
304 if (ext_op == X509V3_ADD_DELETE) {
305 if (!sk_X509_EXTENSION_delete(*x, extidx))
306 return -1;
307 return 1;
308 }
309 } else {
310 /*
311 * If replace existing or delete, error since extension must exist
312 */
313 if ((ext_op == X509V3_ADD_REPLACE_EXISTING) ||
314 (ext_op == X509V3_ADD_DELETE)) {
315 errcode = X509V3_R_EXTENSION_NOT_FOUND;
316 goto err;
317 }
318 }
319
320 /*
321 * If we get this far then we have to create an extension: could have
322 * some flags for alternative encoding schemes...
323 */
324
325 ext = X509V3_EXT_i2d(nid, crit, value);
326
327 if (!ext) {
328 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, X509V3_R_ERROR_CREATING_EXTENSION);
329 return 0;
330 }
331
332 /* If extension exists replace it.. */
333 if (extidx >= 0) {
334 extmp = sk_X509_EXTENSION_value(*x, extidx);
335 X509_EXTENSION_free(extmp);
336 if (!sk_X509_EXTENSION_set(*x, extidx, ext))
337 return -1;
338 return 1;
339 }
340
341 if ((ret = *x) == NULL
342 && (ret = sk_X509_EXTENSION_new_null()) == NULL)
343 goto m_fail;
344 if (!sk_X509_EXTENSION_push(ret, ext))
345 goto m_fail;
346
347 *x = ret;
348 return 1;
349
350 m_fail:
351 if (ret != *x)
352 sk_X509_EXTENSION_free(ret);
353 X509_EXTENSION_free(ext);
354 return -1;
355
356 err:
357 if (!(flags & X509V3_ADD_SILENT))
358 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, errcode);
359 return 0;
360}
